results.description: Woldingham is a village in Surrey located above sea level just within the M25, southeast of London. Situated high on the North Downs between Oxted and Warlingham, it is a village of 2,326 inhabitants (according to the Office for National statistics 2001 census) (...)
results.title: Woldingham

results.description: Oxted is a commuter town in Surrey, England at the foot of the North Downs, north of East Grinstead and south-east of Croydon.  (...)
results.title: Oxted

results.description: Woldingham railway station is in Surrey, in England. Train services are provided by Southern, and the station is on the Oxted Line. The station opened as "Marden Park" and was very simple with one waiting shelter (...)
results.title: Woldingham railway station

results.description: Hurst Green is a large village in the English county of Surrey. The census area of Oxted which includes Hurst Green has a population of 10,812. Hurst Green is very close to Oxted to the north, and the village of Merle Common to the south (...)
results.title: Hurst Green, Surrey
